cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their reasoning about human-understandable concepts. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it presents a method to infer labeled concept data and interpret concepts through a decision tree. Additionally, it may belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as decision trees can provide information about how concepts interact with each other, which is relevant to language understanding. Finally, it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it deals with neural networks and their interpretability.
